data.content:
Three things break. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö expression tree no longer needed

`ExecuteUpdateAsync` now takes `Action<...>` instead of `Expression<Func<...>>`. Your manual expression tree construction won't compile. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö uniquified & full-path prefixed

Two changes hit you:

- **Shared property names** (e.g. `Street` on both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress`) now get a numeric suffix to disambiguate. A migration will rename columns.
- **Nested complex types** now use the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

To preserve existing column names, pin them explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b => {
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa => {
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba => {
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b => {
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p => {
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba => {
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods like `CommandReaderExecuting` now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter (redacted SQL)
    { /* logging ŌĆö use logCommandText for safe log output */ }
}
```

Update every method in the interface similarly ŌĆö `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc. all gain the same parameter.
